      <description>&lt;h1 id=&#34;adugo-the-game-of-the-jaguar-and-dogs&#34;&gt;Adugo: The Game of the Jaguar and Dogs&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Adugo, also known as &amp;ldquo;Jaguar and Dogs,&amp;rdquo; is a traditional game played by the &lt;a href=&#34;https://pib.socioambiental.org/en/Povo:Bororo&#34;&gt;Bororo&lt;/a&gt; people in Brazil. This game simulates a hunting scenario and shares similarities with other strategic games from Southeast Asia.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id=&#34;overview-of-the-game&#34;&gt;Overview of the Game&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Adugo is played on a board where the black piece represents the &lt;strong&gt;jaguar&lt;/strong&gt;, and the white pieces represent the &lt;strong&gt;dogs&lt;/strong&gt;. The game is an asymmetrical strategy challenge, where each side has distinct goals and abilities.





    
